  "doc_id": "5241",
  "text": "The idea of re-adapting motion plans when finding new unexpected obstacles has been exploited significantly in the literature. The discrete-time D*, and D* lite algorithms [CITATION_1] , [CITATION_2] re-adapt A* algorithms to find the optimal path in a discretized space. However, these algorithms become intractable as the dimensionality increases. To alleviate the curse of dimensionality, research has been focused on extending sampling-based planners to work in dynamic environments. Another disadvantage of the discrete space algorithms is their limited ability to handle differential constraints.",
